  "text": "In the management of acute episodes in a major depressive disorder, aripiprazole is an established treatment as an add-on to standard antidepressants. However, this is not the case with acute bipolar depression as demonstrated in an RCT in which aripiprazole failed to separate from placebo on the primary efficacy measure of Hamilton Rating Scale for Depression when used with open adjunctive citalopram [CITATION_1] .",
